org.apache.flex.compiler.internal.definitions.references

Class ResolvedReference

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.flex.compiler.internal.definitions.references.ResolvedReference
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IReference

    public class ResolvedReference
extends Object
implements IReference
    Implementation of IReference representing a reference that always resolves to the definition passed to the constructor.

    This is useful for Vector methods, where the return type is the type parameter for the Vector (i.e., T in Vector.<T>. If a Vector method returns T then we know what it is; we don't need to walk up the scope chain to resolve it.
